The Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics ended Sunday night, and many people have found it hard to say goodbye to the athletes and the beloved panda mascot Bing Dwen Dwen. But two real giant pandas, Gong Gong and Shun Shun at Hainan Tropical Wildlife Park and Botanical Garden in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province, accepted a "curling challenge." Staff members used flower peddles and fruits to set up a "curling rink" for them to enjoy the sport. (All photos via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)